## read in PAD data using sf::st_read and here 
ASD_2012_5m <- sf::st_read(here("asds","ASD_2012_5m.shp")) %>% 
  dplyr::select(STASD_N) 
## Reading layer `ASD_2012_5m' from data source 
##   `/Users/elmeraa/Desktop/FORESCE_PAD/FORESSCE_PAD/asds/ASD_2012_5m.shp' 
##   using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 312 features and 3 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -179.1473 ymin: 18.91746 xmax: -66.9499 ymax: 71.35256
## Geodetic CRS:  NAD83
plot(ASD_2012_5m)

## read in FORESCE tif file to serve as a template to fasterize by 
template <- raster(here("FORESCE2050A1B_eco_4_Level_3_2013_us_extent.tif"))

## use st_transform to make sure both files have the same crs codes to fasterize by 
ASD_2012_5m <- st_transform(
  ASD_2012_5m,
  crs=st_crs(template)
)


ASD_2012_5m$STASD_N = as.numeric(ASD_2012_5m$STASD_N) 

## now lets fasterize! 
raster <- fasterize(
  sf = ASD_2012_5m,
  raster = template,
field = "STASD_N")
## plot results 
plot(raster)

## export as tif 
raster::writeRaster(
   raster,
   "ASD_2012_5m.tif",
   overwrite = TRUE
   )
